    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>4 hard-boiled eggs, peeled and halved</li>
            <li>1 cup grated coconut</li>
            <li>1 large onion, finely chopped</li>
            <li>2 tomatoes, chopped</li>
            <li>1/4 cup vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon mustard seeds</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon cumin seeds</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder (adjust to taste)</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon coriander powder</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon garam masala</li>
            <li>Curry leaves</li>
            <li>Salt, to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh cilantro for garnish</li>
            <li>Cooked rice or roti for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a blender, grind grated coconut, chopped onions, and tomatoes into a smooth paste. Set aside.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a pan over medium heat. Add mustard seeds and cumin seeds. Once they splutter, add curry leaves and ginger-garlic paste. Saut√© for a minute.</li>
            <li>Add the coconut-onion-tomato paste to the pan. Cook until the oil starts to separate from the masala.</li>
            <li>Stir in turmeric powder, red chili powder, coriander powder, garam masala, and salt. Mix well and cook for a few more minutes.</li>
            <li>Add the hard-boiled egg halves to the curry, ensuring they are well coated with the coconut masala. Simmer for 5-7 minutes.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve the Egg Curry with Coconut hot with rice or roti.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Egg Curry with Coconut!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

